<HEADLINE> Dow Falls 149; Nasdaq Drops 115  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 149
points in today's early going. Losing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold an 8-3 lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 115 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down 18 points.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street's early tumble comes courtesy of some new readings
on the U.S. economy.
</P>
<P>
   Those readings show the economy remained rather strong in the
first quarter, while inflationary pressures began to build.
</P>
<P>
   News of inflation is never received very well on Wall Street
because it tends to cut into the return on most investments.
</P>
<P>
   And it also suggests that the Federal Reserve will have to
engineer more interest rate hikes to prevent inflationary pressures
from building even further.
</P>
<P>
   Aside from the economic news, shares in AT&AMP;T's wireless unit
begin trading today on the NYSE, after the biggest initial public
offering in U.S. history.
</P>
