<HEADLINE> Air Force Offers Extra $5,000 Bonus  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Air Force, seeking to put more recruits on
active duty this spring, is offering an extra $5,000 bonus for
enlistees in certain career fields who agree to report by the end
of May.
</P>
<P>
   The money, which is in addition to other existing enlistment
bonuses, is for those who already have shipped out to basic
training or are scheduled to ship out between April 17 and May 31.
Also eligible are those who signed up to enter basic training on or
after June 1 but are now willing to move up their date to May 31 or
earlier.
</P>
<P>
   The money is paid after recruits finish their technical training
in one of about 100 specialized career fields.
</P>
<P>
   The Air Force has fallen short of its recruiting goals in recent
months.
</P>
</TEXT>
