<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 3:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
Thursday, April 27, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   AT&AMP;T Wireless IPO Has Strong Start
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock of AT&AMP;T Wireless Group was up a bit from
its IPO price of 29{ this afternoon, trading up 2{ at 32. In
offering the stock, AT&AMP;T created the largest public offering in
U.S. history, selling $10 billion worth of shares. The modest
response was in contrast to the soaring prices of some IPOs earlier
this year.
</P>
<P>
   Dow Down 23; Nasdaq Up 113
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Blue-chip stocks were mostly lower today after
government reports showed the economy continues to grow -- at the
price of higher wages and benefits. Traders had nervously
anticipated today's economic reports, fearful that one or both
would show that the economy was growing much too fast for the Fed
and would prompt a hike in interest rates. Just before 3 p.m. EDT,
the Dow industrials were down 23.66 at 10,921.84. On the NYSE,
decliners led advancers 1,683-1,168. The Nasdaq was up 113.93 at
3,744.02.
</P>
<P>
   Financial Figures
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures just before 3 p.m. EDT:
Dow Industrials:        10921.84  - 23.66
