<HEADLINE> The Seven Seas Wins Bewitch Stakes  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- The Seven Seas rallied from last place to
beat Innuendo by 2{ lengths Thursday in the $113,100 Grade III
Bewitch Stakes for fillies and mares at Keeneland.
</P>
<P>
   The Seven Seas, ridden by Alex Solis, ran 1{ miles in 2:29 1-5
and paid $11.80, $5.80 and $4.80. Innuendo returned $4.80 and
$4.20, and Hollywood Baldcat paid $5.80 to show.
</P>
<P>
   The Seven Seas, the 4-year-old daughter of El Gran Senor owned
by Charles Kenis and trained by Robert J. Frankel, has three
victories in seven career starts. She earned $70,122 to increase
her career total to $148,147.
</P>
</TEXT>
