<HEADLINE> Defense Secretary To Visit Kosovo  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Defense Secretary William Cohen will visit
U.S. troops on peacekeeping duty in Kosovo next week with Gen.
Henry H. Shelton, chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, the
Pentagon announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Cohen and Shelton will visit Kosovo on Monday and then attend a
ceremony Tuesday in Stuttgart, Germany, marking Air Force Gen.
Joseph Ralston's takeover from Army Gen. Wesley Clark as commander
of U.S. European Command.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday Cohen and Shelton will be in Mons, Belgium, at
Supreme Headquarters Allied Powers Europe, for a ceremony to make
Ralston NATO's top commander in Europe, replacing Clark, who is
retiring. The commander of U.S. European Command traditionally
serves also as top NATO commander.
</P>
<P>
   Cohen will return to Washington on Wednesday.
</P>
