<HEADLINE> Kings' Laperriere Has Knee Surgery  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Los Angeles Kings forward Ian Laperriere had
surgery Thursday to repair a torn ACL in his left knee.
</P>
<P>
   Laperriere, 26, is expected to be ready for training camp in
September.
</P>
<P>
   Laperriere had 22 points, including nine goals, in a career-high
79 games this season. He also led the Kings with 185 penalty
minutes, including 21 major penalties that led the NHL.
</P>
<P>
   The Kings acquired Laperriere from the New York Rangers in an
eight-player trade in 1996. Laperriere has 45 goals and 123 points
in seven NHL seasons with the St. Louis Blues, Rangers and Kings.
</P>
<P>
   The Kings were swept in four games by the Detroit Red Wings in
the first round of the playoffs.
