<HEADLINE> Derby Favorite Tosses Rider  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Fusaichi Pegasus, the Kentucky Derby
favorite, tossed an exercise rider and fell but was not injured
during a morning workout Thursday at Churchill Downs.
</P>
<P>
   Trainer Neil Drysdale said the Wood Memorial winner went through
his daily morning trot without a hitch. But as he was being led off
the track, the horse reared onto its hind legs just before reaching
the draw gate. The horse threw exercise rider Nuno Santos to the
dirt, fell to the track and rolled over.
</P>
<P>
   Fusaichi Pegasus got up within seconds, and Drysdale grabbed his
bridle, calmed the colt and led him back to his barn.
</P>
<P>
   ''He was doing superbly, and then he felt so good that he reared
up and sat down,'' Drysdale said. ''It startled him a bit.''
</P>
<P>
   The trainer joked about the horse's eccentric behavior:
</P>
<P>
   ''When he's in California he can really do some tricks. We may
be coming up to them this week,'' Drysdale said. ''Some mornings
he's a perfect gentleman; some mornings he's feeling so good he
doesn't know what to do with himself.''
</P>
<P>
   The Kentucky Derby is May 6.
</P>
</TEXT>
