<HEADLINE> Day care center evacuated after complaints of fumes  </HEADLINE>
AP Photo
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- Authorities evacuated a day care center with
130 preschool-age children Thursday after hearing complaints that
fumes had made it difficult for some to breathe.
</P>
<P>
   All 130 children and 36 adults at Centre Inc. Day Care were
taken to hospitals as a precaution after the 12:10 p.m. incident
but none were injured, said Robert Resetar, a city emergency
coordinator. All were expected to be released, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Four children and one adult had complained that the fumes
smelled of cleaning fluid and made it difficult to breathe, Resetar
said. Officials took everyone to the hospital because many of the
children were younger than 2 and unable to communicate their
symptoms.
</P>
<P>
   State environmental officials found no source of the odor.
</P>
