<HEADLINE> Ex-WNBA Coach Jim Lewis to Fordham  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Former WNBA coach Jim Lewis is the new women's
basketball coach at Fordham, replacing Kevin Morris, who resigned
last month after a 4-24 season.
</P>
<P>
   Lewis coached the Washington Mystics in 1998. He was at George
Mason from 1984-97 and was the school's winningest coach.
</P>
<P>
   Morris' record at Fordham was 79-116. His best season was his
first, 1993-94, when the Rams were 21-9 and made their NCAA
tournament debut.
</P>
